# Bank Management Application üè¶

A **C++ based Bank Management System** simulating core banking operations using **Object-Oriented Programming** and **File Handling**.

> Thiranex Internship ‚Äî Project 2

---

## Features

- ‚úÖ Create Savings & Current Bank Accounts
- ‚úÖ Deposit Money
- ‚úÖ Withdraw Money (with overdraft support for Current accounts)
- ‚úÖ Balance Inquiry
- ‚úÖ Transaction History
- ‚úÖ Interest Application (Savings accounts)
- ‚úÖ Secure PIN-based authentication
- ‚úÖ Persistent data storage using file handling

---

## OOP Concepts Used

| Concept | Where Used |
|---|---|
| **Classes & Objects** | `BankAccount`, `SavingsAccount`, `CurrentAccount`, `Transaction`, `Bank` |
| **Inheritance** | `SavingsAccount` and `CurrentAccount` inherit from `BankAccount` |
| **Polymorphism** | `withdraw()` overridden in `CurrentAccount` |
| **Encapsulation** | Private/protected members with getters |
| **Abstraction** | `Bank` class hides internal logic from `main()` |

---

## File Handling

- `accounts.dat` ‚Äî stores all account records (type, number, name, balance, PIN)
- `<AccNo>_txn.dat` ‚Äî stores full transaction history per account
- Data **persists between program runs**

